name: Crunch With Leg Raise
benefits: The crunch with leg raise exercise targets the rectus abdominis and oblique muscles, so that the upper and lower abdominal muscles develop simultaneously.

name: Mountain Climber
benefits: Mountain climber are an effective cardio strengthening workout. It can help you strengthen and develop both upper and lower body muscles.

name: Front to Side Plank
benefits: Being a multi-functional movement, this exercise targets not only your abdominal muscles but also the spine and buttocks. Plank strengthens and tightens your entire body, improves your posture and balance, reduces body fat and can help speed up your metabolism.

name: Leg Raise
benefits: this exercise targets the rectus abdominus and oblique muscles, it is particularly useful for burning and tightening the lower fat.

name: Bicycle Crunch
benefits: a popular abdominal exercise that offers several benefits for those looking to strengthen their core and improve overall fitness.

name: Leg Scissors
benefits: promotes greater flexibility and mobility. The wide range of motion required for each leg to move in an alternating scissor pattern helps in stretching the muscles, particularly the hip flexors and hamstrings

name: Dragon Flag
benefits: If you’re aiming for a well-defined six-pack, Dragon Flags can help you achieve that goal. The exercise specifically targets the abdominal muscles, contributing to a more chiseled appearance.

name: Cross Crunch
benefits: Cross Crunches primarily target the obliques and the rectus abdominis (the “six-pack” muscles). By engaging these muscles, Cross Crunches help strengthen and tone your core, improving stability and overall strength.

name: Seated Bench Leg Pull-in
benefits: The Seated Bench Leg Pull-In primarily targets the lower abdominals, but it also engages the hip flexors and stabilizer muscles of the core. It can help strengthen the core muscles, improve stability, and enhance lower abdominal definition.

name: Heel Touch
benefits: The exercise works up the obliques, abs, and lower back muscles. Obliques are the muscles which connects your lats and abs these muscles help in twisting or turning our upper body. This exercise, which targets the oblique muscles, is very useful for tightening and developing the abdominals fat.

name: Decline Sit-up
benefits: Decline sit-ups target the rectus abdominus and oblique muscles to strengthen the core muscles. It is an exercise that you can apply to shape the upper abdominal muscles and six pack muscles.

name: Table Inverted Row
benefits: The inverted row can be a good alternative to the bent-over barbell row, when you want a horizontal pulling exercise that takes all the strain off your lower back.

name: Swimming
benefits: Swimming exercise is very useful for strengthening the upper and lower back. You will be exercising the superficial back muscles with every move you do.

name: Bodyweight Row in Doorway
benefits: a versatile and effective exercise that targets your upper body, primarily your back, shoulders, and arms

name: Band Seated Row
benefits: it helps sculpt the upper and middle back, and promotes good posture.

name: Romanian Deadlift
benefits: an excellent exercise for building strength and muscle mass in targeted muscles. They involve a high level of muscle activation, which stimulates muscle growth and development.

name: Chin-Up
benefits: Chin-up is a closed-chain an exercise that works almost all of the muscle groups on the upper body and provides both hypertrophy and strength at body weight. The focus of the chin-ups exercise is on the back and biceps muscles.

name: Seated Biceps Curl
benefits: a great way to strengthen the biceps muscles, which are essential for many sports movements such as throwing, hitting, and grappling.

name: Waiter Curl
benefits: this exercise minimizes forearm and grip involvement, allowing you to focus solely on working the biceps. This isolation can lead to a more effective bicep workout, helping to build strength and size in this muscle group.

name: One Arm Cable Curl
benefits: allow you to target the biceps more effectively, which can help you achieve greater muscle activation and growth in the weaker arm. This can be particularly useful for individuals who have one arm that is weaker than the other.

name: Overhead Cable Curl
benefits: This position is designed to eliminate shoulder involvement and momentum, while targeting the biceps peak. As you curl the weight up, focus on squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement. This will help to maximize muscle activation and promote greater gains in strength and size.

name: Lying High Bench Barbell Curl
benefits: Lying on the bench helps to isolate the biceps muscles by minimizing involvement from other muscle groups, such as the shoulders and back. This isolation allows you to focus specifically on the biceps, ensuring that they are being properly targeted and engaged during the exercise.

name: Hammer Curl
benefits: an effective exercise for targeting the brachioradialis muscle and the biceps muscle in the upper arm.

name: Kneeling Push-Up
benefits: Reduces the intensity of a traditional push-up, making it accessible for those with limited upper body strength, Builds strength in the chest, shoulders, and triceps, creating a foundation for more advanced push-up variations.

name: Dumbbell Press
benefits: Dumbbells allow a deeper stretch and contraction compared to a barbell, engaging the muscles more effectively and promoting flexibility and strength across a wider range of motion.

name: Dumbbell Fly
benefits: Flys complement pressing movements (like bench presses or push-ups) by targeting the chest through a different plane of motion. This balance can help reduce muscle imbalances and improve overall strength symmetry.

name: Chest Dips
benefits: Chest dips are one of the most effective bodyweight exercises for isolating and targeting the lower pectorals. The forward lean during the movement places more stress on the lower part of the pectoralis major, leading to increased strength and size in this region

name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
benefits: The incline bench press targets the upper portion of the chest muscles, which is an area that can be difficult to target with other exercises. If you think your upper chest muscles are not developing, you can include the incline bench press movement in your programs.

name: Machine Butterfly
benefits: The Butterfly exercise specifically targets the pectoralis major, allowing you to concentrate on chest development without significant involvement from other muscle groups. The guided motion of the machine ensures both sides of the chest receive equal work, promoting balanced muscle development.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
benefits: Dumbbell pullover is one of the rare exercises that trains both the front and back of the body at the same time. The main purpose of this exercise is to work the chest and back muscles, in order to strengthen them, and help you gain muscle mass.

name: High Cable Crossover
benefits: The high cable crossover is an excellent exercise for chest development, as it stretches the chest muscles and increases range of motion. The exercise works the lower, inner, and outer areas of the pecs, which helps achieve a well-rounded chest workout and build overall chest strength.

name: Decline Dumbbell Press
benefits: Specifically targets the sternal head, creating a more balanced and sculpted chest, Dumbbells allow for a deeper stretch and greater contraction compared to barbell variations.

name: Lever Incline Hammer Chest Press
benefits: Targets the upper chest muscles for a more defined and sculpted look, Allows for a greater range of motion compared to traditional bench press.

name: Smith Machine Squat
benefits: The Smith machine provides stability, especially for beginners or those recovering from injury. The guided bar path reduces the risk of wobbling or tipping, allowing you to focus more on the movement and less on balance.

name: Curtsy Lunge
benefits: Performing curtsy lunges challenges your balance and stability as you move in a diagonal direction, which helps strengthen the stabilizing muscles around your joints and core.

name: Dumbbell Walking Lunge
benefits: Dumbbell walking lunges are a highly effective exercise for targeting and strengthening various muscle groups in your lower body. The primary muscles worked include the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and calves. Strengthening these muscle groups can improve your ability to perform lower body movements, such as squatting, jumping, and running, with greater ease and power.

name: Bulgarian Split Squat Jump
benefits: Bulgarian Split Squat Jumps require greater muscle activation than traditional squats, especially in the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. This is because they require a rapid stretch-shortening cycle, which causes the muscle fibers to contract more forcefully.

name: Good Morning
benefits: Targets hamstrings, glutes, and spinal erectors, Reinforces proper hip movement patterns crucial for deadlifts and squats.

name: Jump Squats
benefits: Jump Squats are a plyometric exercise. Plyometrics are explosive aerobic moves that increase speed, quickness, and power and they work your whole body.

name: Kettlebell Swings
benefits: Kettlebell swings engage multiple muscle groups simultaneously, including the hips, glutes, hamstrings, core, back, shoulders, and arms. This makes it an excellent full-body exercise that can help you save time while working on multiple areas at once.

name: Leg Press
benefits: The leg press allows you to use heavy weights, which can promote muscle hypertrophy (growth) in the lower body. If your goal is to add volume to your legs, leg press is one of the best leg exercises that focus solely on the big leg muscles.

name: Leg Curl
benefits: Leg curls are an effective exercise for increasing lower body strength, particularly in the hamstrings. Strengthening these muscles can contribute to improved athletic performance in activities such as running, jumping, and squatting.

name: Leg Extension
benefits: Leg extensions can help enhance the definition and shape of the quadriceps muscles. As the quadriceps become stronger and more developed, they can contribute to a more aesthetic appearance of the legs.

name: Standing Dumbbell Shoulder Press
benefits: The standing dumbbell shoulder press is a compound exercise, meaning it involves multiple joints and muscle groups. This results in more muscle fibers being recruited, contributing to greater overall shoulder muscle development.

name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
benefits: The primary benefit of dumbbell lateral raises is the targeted development of the lateral deltoids, which are the muscles on the sides of your shoulders. By regularly performing this exercise, you can increase the size, strength, and definition of these muscles, contributing to a more sculpted and well-rounded shoulder appearance.

name: 45 Degree Incline Row
benefits: The 45-degree incline row is a compound exercise, which means it engages multiple muscle groups and joints. Compound exercises are effective for building overall strength and muscle mass, as they allow for more weight to be lifted and more muscles to be worked in a single movement.

name: Standing Close Grip Military Press
benefits: The Close Grip Military Press is a compound exercise that engages multiple muscle groups in the upper body, including the triceps, deltoids, upper back, and core. It promotes overall upper body strength and stability, helping you develop pressing strength and power.

name: Scott Press
benefits: By targeting all three heads of the deltoid at once, the Scott Press ensures balanced shoulder development. This can lead to improved aesthetics, symmetry, and strength in the shoulder region.

name: Weight Plate Front Raise
benefits: The Weight plate front raise is a isole exercise that targets the fronts and sides of the shoulders. Suitable for all levels, this shoulder flexion exercise is a good option for building strength, improving shoulder mobility and shaping your shoulder heads.

name: Push-down
benefits: As the triceps become stronger and more toned, your arms’ overall appearance will improve. Well-developed triceps add definition to your arms, giving them a more sculpted and aesthetically pleasing look.

name: Seated Dumbbell Triceps Extension
benefits: Seated Dumbbell Triceps Extension is a single joint isolating exercise that provides strength and muscle development. Overhead extension movements are particularly useful in targeting the long head of the triceps muscle.

name: Dumbbell Skull Crusher
benefits: The skull crusher is an isolation exercise that works the triceps muscle. You can incorporate this exercise into your workouts to tighten flabby arms and tone your arm muscles.

name: Cable Rope Overhead Triceps Extension
benefits: The cable rope overhead triceps extension exercise works the tricep muscle by reaching behind your neck and helping build stronger and bigger arms.

name: Lever Triceps Dip
benefits: Lever Triceps Dip is an compound triceps exercise that increases arm strength and develop arm muscles. Although the focus is on the triceps muscles, it also works the chest, shoulder and back muscles.

name: Triceps Dips on Floor
benefits: Triceps dips on floor are a compound exercise as they worked multiple muscle groups simultaneously. Although this bodyweight exercise mainly targets the triceps, it also hits your chest and front of your shoulder.
